HEADWORD: Dipsomania
<hw>Dip`so*ma"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ thirst + <?/ mania.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid an
uncontrollable craving (often periodic) for drink, esp. for alcoholic
liquors; also improperly used to denote acute and chronic
alcoholism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

